summary: A FedEx Express legal department letter responding to a subpoena request from the U.S. Attorney's Office in West Palm Beach, providing business records on a CD related to FEC File #35777 and Grand Jury 07-103. The letter offers additional delivery records from the past 25 months and requests specifics for further searches.

events.title: FedEx Subpoena Response Submission
events.description: FedEx Express Legal Department submits a CD containing invoices and an Excel spreadsheet of business records in response to a subpoena from the U.S. Attorney's Office in West Palm Beach.

locations: 3620 Haas Cross Road Building 8, 3rd Floor, Memphis, IN 38125
500 S. Australian Avenue, Suite 400, West Palm Beach, FL 33401-6235
keyFacts: FedEx Express responded to a subpoena from the U.S. Attorney's Office in West Palm Beach on February 21, 2008.
The response included a CD with PDF invoices and an Excel spreadsheet containing compiled business records related to FEC File #35777 and Grand Jury 07-103.
FedEx indicated that delivery records are available for the past 25 months, and searches beyond that require a manual process.
The letter requests specific tracking numbers, ship dates, and time frames for any additional searches.
This document shows federal investigators subpoenaing shipping records as part of Grand Jury 07-103, which appears to be an Epstein-related investigation.
